parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auto park brake system can cause the emergency brake to engage unexpectedly, leading to sudden stops, potentially causing accidents or injuries, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The auto park brake system engages unexpectedly
the emergency brake light comes on intermittently
the vehicle comes to a sudden stop
the brake system fails while driving or parked

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auto park/emergency brake system can cause the vehicle to halt to a complete stop without warning, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: the vehicle suddenly stops or becomes difficult to move
the hydraulic reservoir is nearly empty
the pressure switch on the hydraulic system leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pump reservoir seals can cause the automatic braking system (ABS) to engage without warning, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: the vehicle halts to a complete stop
the brake pump reservoir seals fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected loss of engine power can lead to a loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: engine restarts after a delay (up to 4 hours)
gas tank reads full despite actual fuel level

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel system can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Gas tank reads full despite actual fuel level

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty crankshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
The power steering gear box coming loose while driving can cause the front wheels to become misaligned, leading to uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The power steering gear box becomes loose
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving.
